In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @Onion{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Core, deseed, and dice @Long Green Pepper{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Heat a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @Tomato Paste{1}, @Mexican Spice Blend{2%tablespoon}, and @salt{1%tsp}. Season generously with @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir @Crushed Tomatoes{1}, @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{2}, @Kidney Beans{1} and their liquid, and @water{1/2%cup} into pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer until thickened, ~{15-18%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Serve rice, chili, @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce}, @Cheddar Cheese{1%cup}, @Sour Cream{6%tablespoon}, and scallions family style and let everyone build their own bowl.